[SN]TITLE[SN]
Prince William air ambulance rescue girl 'critical' in hospital

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A girl flown to hospital by Prince William after she was hit by a car in Bedfordshire is in a critical condition, police have said.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The nine-year-old girl is being treated for a broken pelvis and legs after the accident in Linslade, Leighton Buzzard.
She is being cared for at Addenbrooke's Hospital in Cambridge.
The Duke of Cambridge, who recently began a job as a co-pilot for the East Anglian Air Ambulance, was pictured at the crash scene on Tuesday.
The girl was walking along Old Road at about 15.40 BST when a blue Mercedes and a silver Ford KA crashed, knocking her over. A second girl received minor injuries.
Anyone who saw what happened has been asked to contact police.
